        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Holman, or 14 miles northeast of Clarksville, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marsena...                        Fort Douglas...
Long Pool Campground...           Witts Spring...
Haw Creek Falls Campground...     Rocky Hill...
Pleasant Valley in Pope County... Moore...
Dabney...                         Tilly...
Crabtree...                       Point Peter...
Lurton...                         Oak Grove in Pope County...
Bohannon...                       Jerusalem...
Imo...                            Hector...
Nogo...                           Treat...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
